According to the ''Gokō-gun Shrine Records,'' the deity "Tenkushine no Ōkumemikoto" was initially treated as a single entity. The ''Shikinaisha Chōsa Hōkoku'' suggests that the deity's name may have been divided into two during the early modern period.

Ōkumemikoto served {{ill|Emperor Jimmu|en|Emperor Jimmu|qid=Q200188|lt=Emperor Jimmu|1=Emperor Jimmu}} and is considered the ancestor of the [[Kume clan]]. The surrounding area, historically known as Kume Village, was home to the Kume clan, and the shrine enshrines their ancestral deity.

